The reality of the Biblical horror unfolding in the Gaza Strip is that both sides are bound together by a strategic complicity -- effectively an iron destiny. Above the tactical level, no serious agency exists for either, unless to surrender which -- of course -- neither will ...
... Partisan Israeli / Palestinian cheerleaders impute agency to the side they oppose, but this is either unintelligent or insincere. Few want to admit the existential chicken game in process. ...

... Israel can only attempt to reinstall deterrence, which now requires quasi-apocalyptic levels of enemy pain. Reciprocally, Hamas can only try to demonstrate invulnerability to the logic of deterrence, by staging a spectacle of martyrdom. ...

... These two strategically mandatory objectives are perfectly complementary, which is why they compose a single fate. Much (profoundly split) spectator moralization of the coming ugliness is equally inevitable. ...
... Sometimes prophecy is very easy -- it's just too dark to be widely acknowledged.
